<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Frequently Asked Questions</title>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Roboto:wght@400;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <link href="styles.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: 'Roboto', sans-serif;
            background-color: #f9fafb; /* Light background */
            color: #374151; /* Darker text */
            line-height: 1.6; /* Increased line height */
            padding: 2rem; /* Increased padding */
        }

        h1 {
            text-align: center;
            color: #086b09; /* Green color */
            font-size: 2.5rem; /* Increased font size */
            margin-bottom: 1.5rem; /* Space below the heading */
            opacity: 0; /* Start hidden */
            animation: fadeIn 1s forwards; /* Apply fade-in animation */
        }

        @keyframes fadeIn {
            from {
                opacity: 0; /* Start fully transparent */
                transform: translateY(-20px); /* Start slightly higher */
            }
            to {
                opacity: 1; /* End fully opaque */
                transform: translateY(0); /* End in original position */
            }
        }

        h3 {
            background-color: #e0f2fe; /* Light blue background */
            border-radius: 0.5rem; /* Rounded corners */
            padding: 15px; /* Padding for headers */
            font-size: 1.25rem; /* Increased font size */
            margin: 1rem 0; /* Space above and below */
            cursor: pointer; /* Make the heading clickable */
            transition: background-color 0.3s ease, transform 0.2s; /* Smooth background color change */
        }

        h3:hover {
            background-color: #bfdbfe; /* Slightly darker blue on hover */
            transform: translateY(-2px); /* Slight lift effect on hover */
        }

        p {
            margin-bottom: 1rem; /* Increased margin */
            display: none; /* Hide answers by default */
            font-size: 1rem; /* Increased font size */
            padding: 10px; /* Padding for answers */
            background-color: #ffffff; /* White background */
            border-left: 4px solid #1d4ed8; /* Blue left border */
            border-radius: 0.5rem; /* Rounded corners */
            transition: max-height 0.3s ease, opacity 0.3s ease; /* Smooth transition */
            overflow: hidden; /* Hide overflowing content */
            opacity: 0; /* Start hidden */
            max-height: 0; /* Set initial max height to zero */
        }

        .faq-item.active p {
            display: block; /* Show answers when active */
            opacity: 1; /* Fade in */
            max-height: 100px; /* Set a max height for transition */
        }

        .container {
            max-width: 800px; /* Increased width */
            margin: 0 auto;
            background-color: #ffffff;
            padding: 2rem; /* Increased padding */
            border-radius: 0.5rem;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }

        .button-container {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            margin-top: 2rem; /* Add some space above the button */
        }

        .back-button {
            background-color: #08a01a; /* Green background */
            color: white; /* White text */
            padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem; /* Padding for the button */
            border: none;
            border-radius: 0.5rem; /* Rounded corners */
            cursor: pointer; /* Change cursor on hover */
            text-align: center;
            text-decoration: none; /* Remove underline */
            font-weight: bold; /* Make text bold */
            transition: background-color 0.3s ease; /* Smooth background color change */
        }

        .back-button:hover {
            background-color: #1e40af; /* Darker blue on hover */
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>

        <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 onclick="toggleAnswer(this)">What is Scruter?</h3>
            <p>Scruter is your local platform for buying, selling, and discovering everything you need. Whether it's products, services, or community activities, we connect people for a better local experience.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 onclick="toggleAnswer(this)">How can I buy or sell items on Scruter?</h3>
            <p>You can create an account, list your items for sale, or browse items available in your local area through our user-friendly interface.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 onclick="toggleAnswer(this)">Is there a fee for using Scruter?</h3>
            <p>Scruter is free to use for buying and selling. However, we may charge a small fee for premium listings or features in the future.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 onclick="toggleAnswer(this)">How can I contact customer support?</h3>
            <p>If you have any questions or need assistance, you can reach our customer support team at scruter@gmail.com or call us at 999999999.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 onclick="toggleAnswer(this)">What should I do if I encounter a problem with a transaction?</h3>
            <p>If you experience any issues with a transaction, please contact our support team immediately, and we will assist you in resolving the matter.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 onclick="toggleAnswer(this)">Can I edit or delete my listings?</h3>
            <p>Yes, you can edit or delete your listings anytime through your account dashboard.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 onclick="toggleAnswer(this)">How can I reset my password?</h3>
            <p>If you've forgotten your password, you can reset it by clicking on the "Forgot Password?" link on the login page and following the instructions.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 onclick="toggleAnswer(this)">What payment methods are accepted on Scruter?</h3>
            <p>We accept various payment methods, including credit/debit cards and popular online payment systems. Specific payment options will be listed at checkout.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 onclick="toggleAnswer(this)">Can I leave reviews for buyers or sellers?</h3>
            <p>Yes! After completing a transaction, you can leave reviews for buyers or sellers based on your experience to help others make informed decisions.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 onclick="toggleAnswer(this)">Is my personal information safe on Scruter?</h3>
            <p>Yes, we take your privacy seriously. We use industry-standard security measures to protect your personal information. Please review our privacy policy for more details.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 onclick="toggleAnswer(this)">How do I report a user or listing?</h3>
            <p>If you encounter suspicious activity or listings, please contact our support team with the details, and we will investigate the matter promptly.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 onclick="toggleAnswer(this)">Can I access Scruter from my mobile device?</h3>
            <p>Yes, Scruter is optimized for mobile use, so you can browse, buy, and sell items directly from your smartphone or tablet.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="button-container">
            <a href="/" class="back-button">Back to Home</a>
        </div>
    </div>

    <script>
        function toggleAnswer(element) {
            const answer = element.nextElementSibling; // Get the answer (next <p> element)
            const faqItem = element.parentElement; // Get the parent FAQ item
            if (answer.style.display === "none" || answer.style.display === "") {
                answer.style.display = "block"; // Show the answer
                faqItem.classList.add('active'); // Add active class for styles
                answer.style.opacity = 1; // Fade in
                answer.style.maxHeight = '100px'; // Set a max height for transition
            } else {
                answer.style.opacity = 0; // Fade out
                setTimeout(() => {
                    answer.style.display = "none"; // Hide the answer after fade out
                    faqItem.classList.remove('active'); // Remove active class
                }, 300); // Match this to the transition duration
            }
        }

        // Optional: Set all answers to be hidden initially
        document.querySelectorAll('.faq-item p').forEach(p => p.style.display = 'none');
    </script>
</body>

</html>
